parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition module can cause the vehicle to fail to start, stall, or even catch fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: the vehicle shuts down without warning
burning of ignition switch and wires in the steering column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank corrosion and leaking can cause fuel to spill onto the road, increasing the risk of fires, accidents, and environmental damage. It can also lead to costly repairs and potentially leave the driver stranded.
